title: Magnitude 7.3 Earthquake Hits Northeastern Japan, Producing Small Tsunamis
sub_head: Dozens of injuries reported, mostly minor; bullet train derails but passengers unhurt
body:
TOKYOâ€”A strong earthquake of estimated magnitude 7.3 hit northeastern Japan late Wednesday, and small tsunamis were recorded in the region.
The quake caused dozens of injuries, mostly minor, according to Kyodo News, and items fell off store shelves. No deaths were reported as of early Thursday.
